==English==
===Etymology===
From the stem of Old English ''[[bugan|būgan]]'' ‘bend, bow’ + ''[[-some]]''.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈbʌksəm/}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# {{archaic}} [[cheerful|Cheerful]], [[lively]], [[happy]].
#:*'''1819''': The Outlaw accordingly led the way, followed by the '''buxom''' Monarch, more happy, probably, in this chance meeting with Robin Hood and his foresters, than he would have been in again assuming his royal state — Walter Scott, ''Ivanhoe''
# Of a woman, having a [[full]], [[voluptuous]] [[figure]]; [[healthy]] and lively.

